messages.content: Has anyone here tried verbally announcing the thoughts that come into your mind while meditating, almost as a symbolic way of flushing them out so that you can carry on focusing on your breath? I've tried it recently and it's made the meditations much more enjoyable and time flew way faster than usual. Thing is I've heard that the deeper the meditation, the slower time should feel, so I wonder if it's actually beneficial
i feel like if i tried that i'd say an idea and just follow that train of thought
like i would say "i need to go finish this memo i was working on" and as i say it, it feels more and more important

I see, well for something like that i would say "work" or "memo", acknowledge the thought, and then move back to breath. I guess being able to abandon trails of thought comes with practice.  I try to keep the speaking down to a minimum (to dwell less on the thoughts) by using single words.

I personally haven't found that I follow trains of thought more than I usually would with this technique, in fact as I've said I've found that it improves the quality of the meditation. Was wondering if other people had tried it or would wanna try it
